&lt;p&gt;This individual is a critical member of the Data Operations team and will act as a strategic partner to investment teams, client service professionals, risk &amp;amp; compliance, and fund administrators as well as partner with technology teams to build APIs and automation tools that streamline data ingestion and transformation. The Data Operations team play a critical role in the firm’s data strategy in alignment with investment, client, and operational goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Strategy &amp;amp; Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion data quality standards and drive adoption of best practices across teams for data integrity, consistency, accuracy, and security across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure scalable and resilient data infrastructure to support reporting, analytics, and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Integration &amp;amp; Automation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead efforts to centralize and automate the aggregation of data from fund administrators, custodians, and other third-party sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development of client reporting, investment dashboards, and operational analytics with accurate and timely data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Quality and Reconciliation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review Portfolio Management System for accuracy and completeness with respect to valuations, commitments, capital calls, distributions, etc. Resolve any reconciliation discrepancies in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review capital calls and distributions across our various vehicles. Ensure accurate and timely notification, reconciliation of incoming funds, and delivery of funds to the relevant third party/parties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Candidate Background:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of Accounting or Operations experience within Hedge Fund, Private Equity/Venture Capital firm or Fund Administrator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required experience with Addepar or other Portfolio Management Accounting System.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AI tools and technologies is a plus. We value team members who are curious about leveraging AI to enhance productivity, streamline workflows, and drive innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of private fund subscription and redemption processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Net Asset Value, Unfunded Commitments, IRR and TWR calculations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel knowledge (construction of pivot tables, and use of VLOOKUPs, SUMIFs and similar formulas).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using SQL, Snowflake or an equivalent data warehouse.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Medical, Dental and Vision Insurance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life and disability insurance coverage as well as family and wellness benefits including mental health benefits, fertility benefits, and back-up childcare.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A matching 401(k) program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commuter Benefits program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stipends to support wellness and hybrid working arrangements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We support employees who wish to pursue professional designations/certifications and offer tuition reimbursement in addition to an allocation for books and other supplies needed for an individual&#39;s coursework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart-casual dress code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Applicants are expected to work onsite in our New York office in accordance with our hybrid working policy.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&l

