&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a sharp, proactive, and highly seasoned Executive Assistant to serve as a true business partner to the Head of ICONIQ Studio. This role goes well beyond traditional administrative support—the ideal candidate is a strategic operator who anticipates needs, drives accountability across stakeholders, and helps keep a fast-moving leader and team on track. Responsibilities span complex calendar and inbox management, relationship and network management, meeting follow-up and execution tracking, and seamless coordination of travel, events, and special projects. Maintaining confidentiality, multitasking effectively, demonstrating exceptional attention to detail, and exhibiting a strong work ethic are imperative for success. A passion for excellence and a no-task-too-big-or-too-small mindset are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a true business partner to the Head of Studio, ensuring seamless flow of day-to-day activities and anticipating needs before they arise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and proactively manage a complex, high-volume calendar across multiple time zones, balancing competing priorities with sound judgment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and prioritize a busy email inbox, drafting responses, flagging what matters, and triaging on behalf of the executive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive relationship management by tracking and strategically planning engagement with internal stakeholders, external partners, and the broader ICONIQ community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture follow-ups, action items, and key takeaways from meetings; proactively chase deliverables across stakeholders to keep workstreams on track&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively capture, enter, and maintain meeting notes, contacts, and other relevant data in Salesforce and other systems to support an institutionalized process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seamlessly coordinate domestic and international travel logistics, meals, vendors, and lodging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively and strategically coordinate internal and external meetings, team events, and meeting materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually create and improve systems and processes around team functionality and operating cadence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Send and track gifts, mailings, and other touchpoints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and process monthly expense reports with accuracy and timeliness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide additional administrative and special project support as needed, including building rapport across the Studio team and partnering closely with colleagues across ICONIQ&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate timely responsiveness outside of “regular” business hours when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Candidate Background:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in an executive support role, ideally supporting a senior leader within Venture Capital, Private Equity, Private Wealth Management, Management Consulting, Investment Banking, or a similarly fast-paced, professional services environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of operating as a true business partner—not just an executor—with the maturity and judgment to represent a senior leader internally and externally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional proactivity, ownership, and follow-through; takes pride in keeping people, projects, and commitments on track&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills, unwavering integrity, and the confidence to engage with all levels of the firm and external stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
