&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Analyst or Associate, Business Development (Talent Pipeline)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Analyst or Associate within our Business Development team, you will help drive the growth of ICONIQ Investment Management by identifying, engaging, and cultivating relationships with prospective clients. Operating at the intersection of relationship development, strategic analysis, and market intelligence, you will play a critical role in helping expand ICONIQ’s community of influential entrepreneurs, executives, investors, and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner closely with colleagues across Business Development, Client Advisory, Investment Management, Capital Markets, and Operations to develop thoughtful outreach strategies, evaluate prospective client opportunities, and support the firm’s long-term growth objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for professionals who are intellectually curious, relationship-oriented, and energized by helping build something exceptional. If you enjoy connecting dots, uncovering opportunities, and partnering with high-performing teams to create meaningful outcomes, this is an opportunity to join a team built on trust, excellence, and uncommon care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given our ongoing talent needs, we are consistently looking for high-quality individuals to join our team.&lt;strong&gt; However, please note that this opening is intended to pipeline candidates for future opportunities, and we will reach out when the timing is right.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities for All Candidates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the Business Development team across a broad range of sourcing, prospecting, relationship development, and strategic initiatives, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting research to identify prospective clients and key relationship opportunities across the firm’s network and target markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring industry developments, fundraising activity, liquidity events, executive transitions, mergers and acquisitions, and other relevant market activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing prospective client balance sheets, investment portfolios, holding structures, and other financial materials to identify areas where ICONIQ can provide value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing prospect materials, relationship summaries, meeting briefs, and customized presentations to support outreach efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining accurate prospect data, activity tracking, and reporting within Salesforce and other business development systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating closely with Client Advisory, Investment Management, Capital Markets, and Operations teams to support prospect engagement efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting special projects, market mapping exercises, strategic analyses, and other growth initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If You Are a Senior Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Analysts take on increasing ownership of sourcing efforts, prospect analysis, and business development initiatives. In addition to the core responsibilities, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently manage prospect research and qualification efforts across priority markets and target client segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop thoughtful analyses of prospective client portfolios and financial situations to help identify opportunities for engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
